<h2>The musicc</h2>
<p>I mostly do trance and its derivatives, preferably with the "classic" and "euro-" prefixes, except when I don't. In that case, I mix everything from house and trance to synthwave and orchestral elements in the weirdest possible ways. Preferred tools are usually <a href="https://lmms.io">LMMS</a> and <a href="https://zynaddsubfx.sourceforge.io">ZynAddSubFx</a>.</p>
<h2>How acquire?</h2>
<p>All of my solo releases (including Trancwolve and Steve Pixus aliases) are available free of charge, with lossless downloads provided on platforms that support it. Go to the Links tab for all the links. The exact format can vary, please check profile/channel descriptions for more information. If you need the original hi-res masters for whatever reason, just hit me up.</p>
<p>If you still feel an overpowering need to support me, you can do it through <a href="https://trancwolve.bandcamp.com">Bandcamp</a>, highly appreciated :3</p>
<h2>Licensing n stuff</h2>
<p>All of my official releases can be found on <a href="https://trancwolve.bandcamp.com">Bandcamp</a>. You are free to use any of those tracks in videos and live broadcasts without my explicit permission, as long as you properly credit me, even where a more restrictive license is indicated. A simple "Artist - Title" line is fine, but linking the source is always appreciated.</p>
<p>Reuploading/redistributing parts or the entirety of any of the tracks by themselves (remixed or not) without my explicit permission is prohibited unless a CC license permitting it is indicated.</p>
<p>Terms for remixes and collabs can be different depending on the people involved, so in that case, it's best to ask me/us first.</p>
